<div id="review_1463342390" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1463342390" />
    <a title="Julie Davis" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2125014-julie-davis"><img alt="Julie Davis" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1277820647p2/2125014.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1463342390?book_show_action=true">Dec 08, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Julie Davis" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Julie Davis" href="/user/show/2125014-julie-davis">Julie Davis</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780679642688" href="/book/show/2708473-purgatory">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2125014-julie-davis?shelf=dante">dante</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2125014-julie-davis?shelf=a-good-story-is-hard-to-find-podcas">a-good-story-is-hard-to-find-podcas</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1463342390" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9557583558514572605">Julie is stuck with the Wrathful. Can&apos;t see a thing. Which is unfortunate because Scott is no help at all, as he is prostrate with the Ava- the Avarish- er, the greedy. Virgil is still around here somewhere. A Good Story is Hard to Find, <a href='http://agoodstoryishardtofind.blogspot.com/2016/07/good-story-137-purgatorio.html' rel='nofollow noopener'>Episode 137</a>: Purgatorio by Dante.<br/><br/>Original comments below.<br/><br/>-----------<br/><br/>Imagine my horror when, upon finishing Esolen&apos;s translation of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1436174569' rel='nofollow noopener'>Inferno</a>, I discovered the library didn&apos;t have Purgatory. Inferno - yes. Paradise - yes. That middle part? Their theory seems to be </span>
  <span id="freeText9557583558514572605" style="display:none">Julie is stuck with the Wrathful. Can't see a thing. Which is unfortunate because Scott is no help at all, as he is prostrate with the Ava- the Avarish- er, the greedy. Virgil is still around here somewhere. A Good Story is Hard to Find, <a href="http://agoodstoryishardtofind.blogspot.com/2016/07/good-story-137-purgatorio.html" rel="nofollow noopener">Episode 137</a>: Purgatorio by Dante.<br /><br />Original comments below.<br /><br />-----------<br /><br />Imagine my horror when, upon finishing Esolen's translation of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1436174569" rel="nofollow noopener">Inferno</a>, I discovered the library didn't have Purgatory. Inferno - yes. Paradise - yes. That middle part? Their theory seems to be Heaven or Hell, with no middle ground.<br /><br />So I made it my December book purchase. Having waited two weeks to <i>get</i> to December and then another week for the used copy to get to me ... I am now extremely happy to have this lovely Modern Library edition in my hands. In many ways my wait to get the book is symbolic of the souls in Purgatory, willing to suffer to achieve ultimate good. I now embark upon my pilgrimage with Dante to turn that crooked road into a straight road by beginning the trip around that mountain. <br /><br />-----------<br /><br />As with the previous time I read Purgatorio, I really loved this book and found it personally inspiring. i was so moved by the very end that I even shed a few tears of joy.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9557583558514572605" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


