        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer193098493" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6747082436995411167">If Dante knew how hard it would be for modern readers to interpret his Commedia, he would have invoked a beautitude of Jesus sung by the angels just for us....&quot;blessed are those who persevere reading Purgatorio....&quot; <br/><br/><br/><br/>Purgatorio is way more complex and interesting than the Inferno - but it requires a lot more effort to read it. I am glad to be done. I will admit that I had help from The Teaching Company DVDs on Dante&apos;s Commedia. I almost feel like I should start it all over again without allowing </span>
  <span id="freeText6747082436995411167" style="display:none">If Dante knew how hard it would be for modern readers to interpret his Commedia, he would have invoked a beautitude of Jesus sung by the angels just for us...."blessed are those who persevere reading Purgatorio...." <br /><br /><br /><br />Purgatorio is way more complex and interesting than the Inferno - but it requires a lot more effort to read it. I am glad to be done. I will admit that I had help from The Teaching Company DVDs on Dante's Commedia. I almost feel like I should start it all over again without allowing too much time to elapse - there's so much to uncover and if you go back you pick up on things after having read ahead. Good stuff! Onto Paradiso! After a short break. Phew.</span>
